content: Completed the story but it won't let me import the data cause apparently I went to jail when I, in fact, did not. Please fix this because I see multiple similar comments.
Could use more chapter art

I actually purchased this book. This is a story about a High School where all the students suddenly gain powers like Clairvoyance, turning invisible, starting fires. The story builds up quite well with a real feeling of being in High school but with everyone having powers. This story has lots of romance options and there is even a prom too. I gave it four stars because there was no real description of how these kids at this high school received these powers.

I loved it, but everytime I try and save my character, so I can continue on in the second book. It tells me I can't continue cause I went to jail. Even though my character wasn't put in jail, she finished her senior year... I don't know what to do.

The game is short, the questions for motives of your actions are too frequent, and the social part of the game is terribly unrealistic. Can this game be entertaining? Maybe. Is it worth the money? Easy no.

There were a lot. Of plot holes and little explanation as to what was going on. Relationships between characters felt unrealistic. And questions pertaining to motive were frequent and repetative. Not worth the money or the time.
The game was really fun and really cute. The lack of mid game save states is a bit annoying if you make mistakes, but otherwise I really enjoyed it
Decent length, and a good amount of options. Pretty good story
Great and quick read.
I really enjoyed this game and want to carry over my save to the second, but I'm unable to even make a save after I finish the first game. Could anyone help me out?
Kinda short needs more to it
I love that game

This was enjoyable ... up until the end. I can't really say much without spoiling it but basically in the ending I got, if you succeed in the main endeavor of the game, it is inexplicably undone during the epilogue and you're just meant to accept that your character did nothing to stop it. Which is exceptionally stupid for a method of story telling that revolves around choices. In spite of that I'd still recommend it if you can get past a possible poorly written ending.
It was a fun game but the ending kind of sucked and made everything i did previously pretty much not count
Think mine is glitched, Taylor always breaks up with me for no reason! What do I keep doing that makes her do that?

The ending (and many plot points) was literally a giant mess. There were so many different inconsistencies and plot holes with the few playthroughs I had. It didnt seem to be caused be inept writing, but rather extremely poor use of the Choice Script used to make these apps. The game did not properly track a staggering amount of choices, to the point I had to re-read many paragraphs of text just to understand what the hell was happening. Completely immersion breaking
cool

It was fun but short. I liked the different endings and the fact I got arrested twice .I wish there was a back button to 're do my choice . But it was worth the 5 dollars I spent a good replay type game. I need to know what happens to veronica and carl
A fun text game, appreciate the level of effort and love shown in its' development. Can't wait for the next episode.

The first playthrough was more than enough for me. Lots of choices were trivial and didn't matter at all, when there could be other important choices that we could have decided for that were not in our control. There are other far superior COG titles out there that you should be buying. (Choice of the Deathless is great, imo.)
One of the best ones
honestly it does don't hold up everything about it is weak af
I am completely unable to refund MH purchase.
Not a highschool sim and hardly a game about being psychic.
So Much Fun!!!!
Very nice.
It's an okay game, I wished there was more to the story like actually going to college and stuff like that.

I don't usually purchase phone games, but choice of games has been giving 
me something I didn't even know I wanted. Even if I don't know the numbers 
behind what constitutes success or failure, every choice seems like it can 
either go horribly wrong or exceptionally well, with a bit of neutrality 
mixed in. I especially enjoy when the choices don't necessarily seem good 
or evil, which is missing from a lot of modern day games that have some 
kind of alignment system. In this game you're just a teen with some powers, 
and choices to make. Most of the characters are well-written, if a bit 
cliched, but otherwise feel real. I look forward to playing it again a 
different way, and getting into their other games too. I thoroughly enjoyed 
my first playthrough, especially despite several moments of nervousness, I 
got the ending that I was hoping for.
Nice Story!
Wish you could choose your gifts :-) but its really cool game

A couple times it wouldn't let me choose any option but the one that continued progress... In one instance there were 5 options and you could pick them all one at a time but it wouldn't let me pick any but the one that said "none I'm good" basically. A game that charges this much shouldn't be messed up in the gameplay the main way you play the game.

The concept of this story is good but for $9 it was a rip-off i read the whole story in 45 minutes so its not very long what i did like was the amount of choices you could make compared to other interactive novels iv played, i dont think its worth the money i paid for it though
Ugh
Great game but I don't think it was worth the $6
This story was absolutely fantastic up until the end. It felt super rushed and the epilogue was unsatisfying

It was a good read, but fairly short. I would have given a higher rating if it took more than 3 hours to read the whole story.
I like the idea of having supernatural power and trying to save the day while having to deal with high school. It's like Life Is Strange. It's a fun interactive novel.

Written well: Target Audience being Adolescents  Its well paced and since ita written for teens the romance is up to level of innocence  The major feedback is you could add relationship stats , so that you can move ahead with your desired character

I loved this game. I feel kinda bummed out that Andrew left me though xD I didn't know he would be pissed off that much about me transforming the principal and clay into model citizens. I mean I sided with him on everything.

I thought u should write longer ending cause after it over I was like huh... that's it? Huh... wow. That didnt explain anything in details. I thought ending should be detail as the beginning. Well 5 star anyway. But I advice making longer and detailed ending that make feel glad or horrible because of my choice make it end that way. ('~' )

I would honestly rather pay to play choice of romance 80+ times than to suggest this game to anyone. I'm really upset that I spent my money for this. I could've bought some moldy kale and ate it, and enjoyed it more than this. Seriously. Don't pay for this.

The fact that when sexual preference is asked you're told that you don't judge at the school, one character has two moms and their are a pair of lesbian cheerleaders is going a bit overboard. Logically speaking 50% of the people in the game being gay isn't  realistic and plan annoying when you're trying to show how "forward thinking" you are. I have no problem with gay people and I'd be just as annoyed if as much attention was being drown to people being straight.

Still worth your money though in my opinion. :)

The central magic mystery made for a great capstone to the story. Splendid work on this adventure overall.

I usually enjoy most of these but I was just not feeling it this time. Maybe it's because I'm a decade out of school and some of it seemed trivial, or maybe it was a newer writer or something. Not bad, but maybe only worth it if you're a teenager.  Still will try to play through again.

I know there have been a few CoGs that have been falling short of the mark; this is NOT one of them. This is perhaps one of my favorites now. I love the premise, the writing, the impact your choices have, the character building, and the long list of possible love interests. You get to balance love, extracurriculars, popularity, and saving your school (for better or worse). What are you waiting for? Go buy it!!

The pacing is a little rushed and a few of the plot points are a bit questionable, but this is a solid interactive story. The author should be proud.  Definitely worth the purchase and I hope to see a sequel!
I'd still give it a buy though I won't go into any details I have been a fan for a long time and it is good

This is definitely a well thought out and gripping story. It is worth the measly payment. However, it does contain a few errors like a page repeating and refers to choices you never made (doesn't affect game as it continues based on your choices still). Also, the story picks up slightly too fast and gets confusing towards the end. Regardless, this one is still worth playing multiple times
